    "created_at": "2016-01-23T23:58:49Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-23T23:59:15Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think the problem can be summarized to \"`AttackCharge` and its related activities are a mess\". I suspect the reason why 4+ didn't work for you has to do with ChargeDelay, which has an internal value of 3. According to my tests, setting a higher ChargeDelay on AttackCharge allows a higher ReloadDelay on the weapon without breaking the firing.\nAnd the fact that the ChargeFire activity performs  Attack.DoAttack before it adds the delay certainly plays a role as well.\n\nLast but not least, the \"Charges: true\" on some weapons seems to have bitrotted, I can't find anything that ties some logic to it.\n"
  },
